WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.502
[ mouse squeaks ]

00:02.586 --> 00:04.003
[ penguins wenk ]

00:06.131 --> 00:07.548
[ all cheering ]

00:10.302 --> 00:11.719
[ screeches ]

00:13.388 --> 00:14.430
♪ Adventure Time ♪

00:14.515 --> 00:16.056
♪ Come on, grab your friends ♪

00:16.140 --> 00:18.518
♪ We'll go to very distant lands ♪

00:18.602 --> 00:20.853
♪ with Jake the dog and Finn the human ♪

00:20.938 --> 00:22.730
♪ the fun will never end ♪

00:22.814 --> 00:24.857
♪ It's Adventure Time ♪

00:26.000 --> 00:32.073
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:33.075 --> 00:36.744
You guys sure you want
another round of squid ink?

00:36.828 --> 00:37.954
[ giggles ]

00:38.038 --> 00:39.330
BOTH:
Ahh!

00:39.414 --> 00:41.415
[ all shouting, grunting ]

00:48.715 --> 00:50.550
[ grunts ]
- Ha ha!

00:50.634 --> 00:52.260
[ strains ]

00:52.344 --> 00:54.095
You're not too bad for a human boy.

00:54.179 --> 00:56.556
Not too bad?
l'm better than that.

00:56.640 --> 00:57.598
Huh?

00:57.683 --> 00:59.684
[ sobbing ]

00:59.768 --> 01:01.561
Rrrr-yah!

01:01.645 --> 01:03.271
Jake, do you hear that?

01:03.355 --> 01:06.983
What'd you say?
Wha! Whoa!

01:07.067 --> 01:09.068
l think someone's crying.

01:09.152 --> 01:12.029
- Rah! Ha ha!
- Stop! This is serious!

01:12.114 --> 01:14.156
l gotta go find out where
that crying is coming from.

01:14.241 --> 01:16.784
Get back here, you chicken!

01:16.868 --> 01:19.870
[jeering ]

01:19.955 --> 01:21.497
What did you call me?

01:21.582 --> 01:24.208
You can'tjust walk away
from a roughhouse!

01:24.293 --> 01:26.586
Hey! Listen up,
you cold-hearted marauders.

01:26.670 --> 01:28.629
Somebody's out there crying for help,

01:28.714 --> 01:30.715
and I'm not gonna ignore that.

01:30.799 --> 01:32.425
Oh, here it comes.

01:32.509 --> 01:34.468
Lay it down, Finn!

01:34.553 --> 01:36.554
A long time ago, when I was a baby,

01:36.638 --> 01:38.347
I went boom-boom on a leaf.

01:38.432 --> 01:39.599
Boom! Boom!

01:39.683 --> 01:42.685
Then I fell backwards and sat
in my own boom-boom.

01:42.769 --> 01:44.145
I cried for a day...

01:44.229 --> 01:45.730
[ sobbing ]

01:45.814 --> 01:48.316
...but no one came to help me.

01:48.400 --> 01:50.568
That day, I vowed to help
anyone in need,

01:50.652 --> 01:53.154
no matter how small their problem.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.239
And that's why I need to go.

01:56.825 --> 01:58.409
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

01:58.493 --> 02:00.453
That's what l'm talking about.

02:00.537 --> 02:02.913
- Yeah!
- Way to go, Finn.

02:02.998 --> 02:04.999
He still cries when he poops.

02:05.083 --> 02:07.877
Thanks for being cool, guys.
Wait up, Finn!

02:07.961 --> 02:10.295
[ sobbing ]

02:10.380 --> 02:11.922
lt's coming from up there.

02:12.007 --> 02:13.966
Someone must be caught
in that avalanche.

02:14.051 --> 02:16.052
Let's get it on.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.803
[ sobbing continues ]

02:22.851 --> 02:25.144
So... who's crying?

02:25.228 --> 02:26.771
l am.

02:26.855 --> 02:29.106
Whoa! Aww. What's wrong, fella?

02:29.191 --> 02:30.650
You crying boulders?

02:30.734 --> 02:31.692
Yes.

02:31.777 --> 02:34.487
l am sad, having been forced to watch

02:34.571 --> 02:37.740
roughhousing men for centuries.

02:37.824 --> 02:39.659
Oh! l see.

02:39.743 --> 02:42.411
You're feeling left out,
and you want to roughhouse, too!

02:42.496 --> 02:44.497
Well, l'll take you on, tough guy.

02:44.581 --> 02:46.207
Come on, back me up, Jake.

02:46.291 --> 02:49.126
Yeah, do it, Finn!
Hit him with a boulder.

02:49.211 --> 02:51.212
And then hit him with another rock.

02:51.296 --> 02:54.173
Please! No roughhousing.

02:54.257 --> 02:56.926
lt m-makes me...

02:57.010 --> 02:59.595
so... sad!

02:59.680 --> 03:01.597
What? Why?

03:01.682 --> 03:04.433
Because they're so rough on each other.

03:04.518 --> 03:06.686
But a smooth,
well-controlled roughhouse

03:06.770 --> 03:08.688
bolsters your guts and, uh...

03:08.772 --> 03:10.439
rejuvenates the muscle.

03:10.524 --> 03:13.192
No! It's raunchy and maddening.

03:13.276 --> 03:18.823
All those men and their
disgusting fantastic bodies.

03:18.907 --> 03:20.908
Whoa. This guy's got problems.

03:20.992 --> 03:21.951
[ gasps ]

03:22.035 --> 03:22.993
[ sobbing ]

03:23.078 --> 03:24.787
Look, Mommy.

03:24.871 --> 03:27.248
Honey, don't look.
That kid's got problems.

03:27.332 --> 03:28.958
[ sobbing continues ]

03:29.042 --> 03:31.585
l'll help you, Mountain.
- Whoa! What?!

03:31.670 --> 03:34.004
l'll stop those roughhousers
from being rough.

03:34.089 --> 03:37.133
Really? You'd do that for me?

03:37.217 --> 03:38.884
Yes, sir. My name's Finn...

03:38.969 --> 03:40.803
and I'm gonna help you out.

03:40.887 --> 03:42.221
But, Finn, we're not gonna

03:42.305 --> 03:43.848
shut down the roughhouse
for real, are we?

03:43.932 --> 03:47.601
No way, but there's got to be
some kind of solution.

03:47.686 --> 03:50.896
l'll figure this out,
Mountain Man, yep.

03:50.981 --> 03:52.356
[ all shouting, grunting ]

03:52.441 --> 03:54.734
Hey, you guys.
- Ah, Finn.

03:54.818 --> 03:56.861
Ready to get destroyed?!

03:56.945 --> 03:58.279
N-No.
[ chuckles ]

03:58.363 --> 03:59.947
Uh, wait. Um...

04:00.031 --> 04:02.992
actually, can you guys
s-stop being so rough?

04:03.076 --> 04:04.994
ALL:
What?

04:05.078 --> 04:07.413
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
What are you talking about, Finn?

04:07.497 --> 04:11.417
Could you... just tone down
the roughhousing a-a little?

04:11.501 --> 04:12.543
- What?
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:12.627 --> 04:14.003
Hey, it's all right, fellas.

04:14.087 --> 04:17.047
Finn, I'm sure this
"tone down the roughhousing" thing

04:17.132 --> 04:19.132
has something to do with your boom-boom,

04:19.216 --> 04:21.218
and I can respect that.

04:21.303 --> 04:24.764
But how can we possibly make
roughhousing less rough?!

04:24.848 --> 04:26.265
[ mouse squeaks, duck quacks ]

04:26.349 --> 04:27.099
[ gasps ]

04:27.184 --> 04:29.894
l think l have a perfect idea.

04:29.978 --> 04:33.314
This will soften your punches
for smooth knockouts,

04:33.398 --> 04:35.524
like punching a dream.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.193
Quack! Quack!

04:37.277 --> 04:38.611
[ squeak! squeak! ]

04:38.695 --> 04:39.653
Ha ha!

04:39.738 --> 04:40.696
Meow! Meow!

04:40.781 --> 04:42.782
Ha ha! Pigs on my knees!

04:42.866 --> 04:44.283
Pigs on my knees!

04:44.367 --> 04:45.576
[ squeal! squeal! ]

04:45.660 --> 04:47.703
- That's like math. Yeah.
- Mathematical.

04:47.788 --> 04:50.039
[ all cheering ]

04:50.123 --> 04:52.792
What do you think?
Fixed all your problems, right?

04:52.876 --> 04:55.252
No! That was terrible.

04:55.337 --> 04:58.005
Now the men are just punching animals.

04:58.089 --> 04:59.799
lt's worse than before,

04:59.883 --> 05:02.802
and it's in no way a good solution.

05:02.886 --> 05:04.929
- I'm sorry.
- Well, you should be.

05:05.013 --> 05:08.015
lt's not fair to those animals
and it's not fair to me.

05:08.099 --> 05:11.352
l might just start to cry again, you know?

05:11.436 --> 05:12.561
[ sobbing ]

05:12.646 --> 05:15.314
- Oh, man.
- Come on, Jake.

05:15.398 --> 05:17.316
l gotta give this another shot.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.443
Finn, this guy seems like a real nutjob.

05:19.528 --> 05:20.569
You know what l mean?

05:20.654 --> 05:22.655
You don't want to get sucked
into this guy's hang-ups.

05:22.739 --> 05:24.657
Yes, I do, Jake.

05:24.741 --> 05:26.700
That's what l vowed --
to help anyone in need,

05:26.785 --> 05:28.744
no matter how small their problem.

05:28.829 --> 05:31.455
[ boom! boom! ]

05:31.540 --> 05:33.290
At least l have to try, brother.

05:33.375 --> 05:34.959
JAKE:
So be it, brother.

05:35.043 --> 05:36.669
[ all shouting, grunting ]

05:36.753 --> 05:38.295
Hey, guys, I'm back.

05:38.380 --> 05:39.171
[ animals bleat, screech, grunt and caw ]

05:40.924 --> 05:42.508
Hey, guys. Guys?

05:42.592 --> 05:43.384
[ growls ]

05:43.468 --> 05:44.677
[ clears throat ]

05:44.761 --> 05:46.554
Men, men, please stop for a second.

05:46.638 --> 05:47.763
Aah!

05:47.848 --> 05:50.975
Men! Boys? Please?
l-I have more to ask of you.

05:51.059 --> 05:51.976
[ slap! slap! slap! ]

05:52.060 --> 05:54.728
Bros? My bros? Brother?

05:54.813 --> 05:57.147
What? Did you just pet me?

05:57.232 --> 05:59.149
I'llpet you.
Pet, pet.

05:59.234 --> 06:00.276
Hey!

06:00.360 --> 06:01.861
Pet, pet.

06:01.945 --> 06:04.613
Hey, this is great!

06:04.698 --> 06:06.532
Hey, did you just pet me?

06:06.616 --> 06:09.201
- Yeah! l did!
- Well, I'm petting you back.

06:09.286 --> 06:10.953
W-Whoa.

06:11.037 --> 06:12.121
W-What the...

06:12.205 --> 06:13.581
this is awesome!

06:13.665 --> 06:14.665
[ both laugh ]

06:14.749 --> 06:17.042
All right! This could be it.

06:17.127 --> 06:18.419
[ grunting ]

06:18.503 --> 06:20.838
[ pat! pat! ]

06:20.922 --> 06:23.132
[ pat! pat! pat! pat! ]

06:23.216 --> 06:26.468
[ pat! pat! pat! ]

06:26.553 --> 06:27.386
[ laughs ]

06:27.470 --> 06:29.179
Finn -- ha ha ha! --

06:29.264 --> 06:31.307
you're really mixing things up

06:31.391 --> 06:33.142
in the best of ways today.

06:33.226 --> 06:35.603
Maybe you can
solve everyone's problems,

06:35.687 --> 06:37.438
like a cherub with his bottom out.

06:37.522 --> 06:39.148
[ laughs ]
Okay, cool.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.900
Hey, I'm gonna go tell the mountain.

06:40.984 --> 06:42.610
All right. I'm gonna...

06:42.694 --> 06:44.528
Mm! Ahh! Mm!

06:44.613 --> 06:46.405
l'm gonna stay here this time.

06:46.489 --> 06:47.531
[ laughs ]

06:47.616 --> 06:50.367
So everything's fine this time, right?

06:50.452 --> 06:52.661
Yes! Thank you, Finn.

06:52.746 --> 06:55.205
So the mountain is totally fine
with everybody petting.

06:55.290 --> 06:57.291
l feel great.
- Right on, man.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.668
The marauders are going crazy
over the petting.

06:59.753 --> 07:02.463
They're petting each other raw.
Check 'em out.

07:02.547 --> 07:04.089
[ all groaning ]

07:04.174 --> 07:05.633
That's -- okay.

07:05.717 --> 07:07.885
T-That's -- yeah, that's fine.

07:07.969 --> 07:09.970
They look kind of... rashy.

07:10.055 --> 07:11.388
MARAUDER:
Hey, Finn!

07:11.473 --> 07:14.350
Hey, man, uh, as you can see,
the petting got sort of...

07:14.434 --> 07:16.435
out of hand.

07:16.519 --> 07:18.520
Stop that!
We are done with that!

07:18.605 --> 07:20.606
We're going back to roughhousing.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.982
No, wait, fellas.

07:22.067 --> 07:24.068
T-The mountain doesn't like roughhousing.

07:24.152 --> 07:26.403
Well, wedon't like
not roughhousing.

07:26.488 --> 07:27.780
You see the problem here?

07:27.864 --> 07:29.865
Well, what if...

07:29.950 --> 07:33.661
what if we rotate the entire mountain
180 degrees around

07:33.745 --> 07:36.080
so the mountain's facing the other direction?

07:36.164 --> 07:37.790
That way, you guys
can keep roughhousing,

07:37.874 --> 07:40.209
and the mountain
doesn't have to watch it.

07:40.293 --> 07:41.961
Sounds fine with me.

07:42.045 --> 07:43.087
What do you say, Mountain?!

07:43.171 --> 07:44.880
That's okay.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.882
Only if you guys promise to stay healthy

07:46.967 --> 07:49.677
and not roughhouse after you rotate me.

07:49.761 --> 07:51.261
That mountain can talk?

07:51.346 --> 07:54.223
Just promise him anything.
He's out of his gourd.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.558
Uh... yeah, we'll stay healthy.

07:56.643 --> 07:59.103
Oh-ho! Thank goodness!

07:59.187 --> 08:02.731
All right, kids,
spin me the math around.

08:02.816 --> 08:06.110
Now l just need to set up
some sort of pulley system.

08:06.194 --> 08:08.570
WOMAN:
No! Over here!

08:08.655 --> 08:10.698
Don't turn him around!

08:10.782 --> 08:13.742
lf you do, l'll miss
looking at his beautiful back.

08:13.827 --> 08:15.411
lt's gorgeous!

08:15.495 --> 08:18.664
Huh? What? Really?

08:18.748 --> 08:21.041
What?! Uh, but -- ugh.

08:21.126 --> 08:23.127
Okay, um, maybe what we can do is --

08:23.211 --> 08:24.837
BOTH: Excuse me.
- Huh?

08:24.921 --> 08:26.714
BOTH:
We need your help.

08:26.798 --> 08:29.842
There's no music playing,
and we desperately want to dance.

08:29.926 --> 08:32.428
Oh, uh, hold on just a second, you guys.

08:32.511 --> 08:34.847
l'll, uh, l'll help you out
in one minute, okay?

08:34.931 --> 08:36.432
Hey! Pipe down over there!

08:36.515 --> 08:38.767
l want some peace and quiet!

08:38.852 --> 08:40.436
Uh, let me just, uh --

08:40.520 --> 08:42.855
- I need to be pollinated.
- Huh?

08:42.938 --> 08:45.774
Pollinated all over to make my babies.

08:45.859 --> 08:48.277
Everybody, please, one problem at a time.

08:48.361 --> 08:49.319
[ growls ]

08:49.404 --> 08:52.156
My butt's itchy,
but l can't scratch it.

08:52.240 --> 08:53.741
This water's too cold.

08:53.825 --> 08:54.783
ALL:
Mommy.

08:54.868 --> 08:57.619
Please keep the flies
away from our mommy.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.329
That guy stole our triangle.

08:59.414 --> 09:01.373
They swiped my plum.

09:01.458 --> 09:03.208
ALL:
[ chanting ] We wanna roughhouse.

09:03.293 --> 09:06.503
l'm naked!
[ laughs ]

09:06.588 --> 09:08.005
What's happening?!

09:08.089 --> 09:09.048
Aaah!

09:09.132 --> 09:11.050
Everybody wants different things,

09:11.134 --> 09:12.760
and some of them want stuff

09:12.844 --> 09:14.636
that's exactly the thing
the others don't want.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.430
Whoa, dude, hold on.

09:16.514 --> 09:18.932
So this guy wants this,
and that guy wants that,

09:19.017 --> 09:21.018
but, man, what do youwant?

09:21.102 --> 09:24.521
[ distorted ]
What do youwant?

09:24.606 --> 09:25.981
[ sobbing ]

09:26.066 --> 09:28.358
What do you want, baby?
Why are you crying?

09:28.443 --> 09:29.735
[ sobbing continues ]

09:29.819 --> 09:31.779
Margaret, this baby won't tell me
what's wrong with it,

09:31.863 --> 09:33.864
and it's stuck to a leaf and it stinks.

09:33.948 --> 09:35.032
Give it here, Joshua.

09:35.116 --> 09:37.451
This baby just needs
some love and kisses to be happy.

09:37.535 --> 09:39.495
Mwah! Mwah-mwah-mwah!
- [ laughs ]

09:39.579 --> 09:41.830
There? See?
Now it's happy.

09:41.915 --> 09:43.582
You just kissed a boom-boom baby,

09:43.666 --> 09:45.292
so don't expect any more
sugar from me, sweetheart,

09:45.376 --> 09:47.211
until we wash your dirty, dirty face.

09:47.295 --> 09:49.296
[ laughs ]

09:49.380 --> 09:51.340
[ gasps ]
Hmm.

09:51.424 --> 09:54.551
Jake, what l want
is to help anyone in need

09:54.636 --> 09:56.637
so everyone is happy.

09:56.721 --> 09:58.013
[ laughs ]

09:58.098 --> 10:01.475
Wow, that's pretty corny, man,
but let's do it, dude!

10:01.559 --> 10:03.352
Whoo-hoo!

10:03.436 --> 10:05.104
Ready over there,
Mushroom Gang?

10:05.188 --> 10:06.396
BOTH:
Ready, Finn!

10:06.481 --> 10:08.774
- Ready, dragon?
- Yes, sir!

10:08.858 --> 10:09.691
Ready, Mountain Man?

10:09.776 --> 10:11.693
[ clears throat ]
l'm ready.

10:11.778 --> 10:14.363
Go!
- [ all grunting ]

10:14.447 --> 10:15.447
[ creak! ]

10:15.532 --> 10:18.575
Hey! The flies are leaving!

10:18.660 --> 10:20.244
[ flies buzzing ]

10:20.328 --> 10:22.371
[ pop! ]
Eh! Can't hear a thing.

10:22.455 --> 10:25.124
- Yahoo! Yeah!
- Yay.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.084
Oh!

10:27.168 --> 10:29.253
[ laughter ]

10:29.337 --> 10:32.923
Pollen! Here they come!

10:33.007 --> 10:34.675
[ laughter ]

10:34.759 --> 10:36.385
[ creak!]

10:36.469 --> 10:39.471
Oh! Yeah!

10:41.474 --> 10:43.559
Yeah-hoo-hoo!

10:45.103 --> 10:47.563
Not naked.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.398
Hey, I can't see anything.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.233
ls anyone roughhousing?

10:51.317 --> 10:52.651
- No.
- Radical.

10:52.735 --> 10:56.405
And I can still see this gorgeous back.

10:56.489 --> 10:58.157
Thank you, Finn.

10:58.241 --> 11:00.242
You really helped everybody.

11:00.326 --> 11:02.911
[ all cheering ]

11:02.996 --> 11:05.247
Stop! I've got a problem.

11:05.331 --> 11:06.290
Well, what's the matter?

11:06.374 --> 11:09.001
This dolphin fell in love with me.

11:09.085 --> 11:10.502
[ dolphin squeaks ]

11:10.587 --> 11:12.337
That's the oppositeof a problem.

11:12.422 --> 11:15.007
Adventure time!

11:20.763 --> 11:24.725
♪ Come along with me ♪

11:24.809 --> 11:28.687
♪ and the butterflies and bees ♪

11:28.771 --> 11:32.691
♪ We can wander through the forest ♪

11:32.775 --> 11:36.695
♪ and do so as we please ♪

11:36.779 --> 11:40.741
♪ Come along with me ♪

11:40.825 --> 11:43.410
♪ to a cliff under a tree ♪

